{
  "stem": "18281.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 149.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the ones that got arrested in Austria, first of all, they dragged retail stores-- they dragged them out of their stores.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They made them wash the floor on the street.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Today in the center of Vienna, there's a monument that shows a Jew washing with a brush, washing the floor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm afraid to tell you that the dogs like that little monument very much.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Also, the tourists sit on it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Viennese put some barbed wire on the poor fellow's back in order to deter tourists from sitting on his back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the dogs still kind of do their business on it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Austrian government.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not the Austrian people, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you have different reasons for not only the Austrians, but I would say the Catholic Central European has been nourished by the tales of the Jew killer for centuries.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only recently, I believe it was in 1956, has the Vatican made a declaration that is called nostra aetate, which states that the Jews of then, 2,000 years ago, and the Jews of today are not responsible for the sufferings of Jesus.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it took an Auschwitz for the Vatican to make such a declaration.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is one part of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jew was always being used as a scapegoat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When 20 million Europeans died of the pest, the Jews had poisoned, poisoned the wells.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- everybody knew that it was the Jews' fault.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what did you do?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You killed the Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When a raped or murdered girl or child was found anywhere in the woods-- today we know that anybody can be a rapist, a murderer-- it was the Jew that did it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they needed that child for ritual murders.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
